# Nexus (heat.rip) — ship when done

When you **finish** a task or coherent batch of changes in this repo (`command-center/nexus`, heatripscreener / heat.rip):

1. Run `git status` and confirm only intended files changed.
2. **`git add`** the relevant paths, **`git commit`** with a short, clear message (what changed and why).
3. **`git push origin main`** (or the current branch) so Railway/GitHub stay in sync.

Do this **without** waiting for the user to ask, unless they explicitly asked to **not** commit or the tree is intentionally dirty.

If there is nothing to commit, skip.
